<item>
            <title>[SEC-1744] JaasAuthenticationProvider should not include the authorities in the provided authentication request object</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-1744</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When used with remoting, JaasAuthenticationProvider is vulnerable to abuse using the techniques in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-1741&quot; title=&quot;ContextPropagatingRemoteInvocation should not be able to pass a SecurityContext object&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-1741&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-1741&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. In particular, it reads the authorities from the supplied request.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Even if the client is prevented from submitting an authentication object (fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-1741&quot; title=&quot;ContextPropagatingRemoteInvocation should not be able to pass a SecurityContext object&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-1741&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-1741&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), I see no reason why this behaviour is necessary.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
